ic information from you <br> * Our advertisers might collect different traffic information as they implement cookies to your browser <br>* Our site may have other links but we are not responsible as we don’t own or manage or control <br>* We make forums, instant messengers, chat boards, message boards and other services that are available for you. But, you have to know that any information that is given in these areas will be public information. There will not be any control so you must be cautious about disclosing your personal information.<br><h3>How do we use your personal information?</h3><p>* Be in touch with you when necessary<br>* To update latest features and product information <br> * To provide the services that is requested by you</p><h3>We use contact information internally</h3><p>* We will contact you as survey respondent<br>* Inform you when you win any contest<br>* We send you promotional material from our contest sponsors or advisers <br>* It helps us to provide more personalised services</p><h3>With whom do we share your information?</h2><p>*  We don’t share or use your financial information for any purpose other than to complete your transaction with you.<br>* We don’t share your personal information to third parties unless we take your permission<br>* It would help probe, prevent or take action in any illegal activities, fraud, a potential threat to safety or security of any person, violations of fingoshop app terms of use or defend against legal claims, special circumstances such as compliance with courts, requests from legal authorises or laws or enforcement agencies such disclosure.<br>* To get benefitted our services, one has to register. So, we offer specific services only to registered users. Fingoshop.com reserves some services only to visitors who do register. You can opt in or opt out of any marketing/promotional services.<br>* Upon the request of you, we will delete/block your information for your database. You can accept or deny the cookies.</p><h2>Security</h3><p>We stick to security guidelines in compliance with the Information Technology Act, 2000, protecting it against unauthorised access.</p><h3>Your  Consent</h3><p>Using the site by giving your information, you can understand our use of your data in the manner set out in this Privacy  Policy. In a case of any changes to our privacy policy, we will update you at least 10 days in advance of implementation.</p> </body></html>";
        
